column2: Notice to all DMF users

column1:
Information Security
 Guidelines for Use and
 Protection of Limited
 Access DMF Information

List of Persons Certified
 to Receive the Limited
 Access Death Master File
<script language="JavaScript">zSetTitle('Limited Access Death Master File Weekly Updates');</script>
The following DMF (weekly) updates are available for the current quarter.  Update data is
not cumulative. Therefore, it may be necessary to download more than
one file, and apply them in chronological order.  Failure to apply all files
in the proper order will result in a corrupt or incorrect master list.
Also note that both the ASCII and EBCDIC versions are available; however,
it is only necessary to download the version corresponding to your master
For your convenience, MD5 checksums for each file are listed below.  These
may be used to verify that you have successfully completed your download.
In order to verify these checksums, you will need to obtain an MD5 sum
generator. For your convenience, one is available through the Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) page. If the MD5 sum generated by the program does not match the one for the
corresponding file below, please retry your download.

Notice from Social Security Administration regarding Death Master File Update Schedule: Death Master File Weekly Updates should be available on each Saturday of the month but can be delayed until the following U.S. Government business day.
